  "version": "1.1",
  "_notes": [
    "Application rates are conservative starting figures drawn from common horticultural references (Rodale, RHS, USDA Extension fact sheets). Real-world rates vary with soil type, organic-matter content, and crop demand; users should verify with local extension advice before bulk application.",
    "ph_effect_per_100g_m2 is the approximate pH shift in a sandy loam at 15 cm depth — conservative for clay (which buffers more), generous for pure sand.",
    "Substances are ordered so that the priority walk picks the most commonly-applicable choice first per fix category.",
    "v1.1 adds eight commercial mineral fertilizers (chemical-generic names) and four structural amendments (Kieselgur/perlite/vermiculite/sand). Mineral entries follow the corresponding organic ones so the organic-preferred tie-breaker keeps its bias unless the user explicitly disables organic preference.",
    "Label-derived entries verified by user: slow_release_lawn_fertilizer_ibdu (IBDU, Compo Floranid line), ammonium_sulfate_nitrate (13% S elemental — German label states 'S wasserlöslicher Schwefel'; EU labeling requires the SO3 qualifier when SO3 equivalents are meant), single_superphosphate (single SSP, 18% P2O5 + 11% S — confirmed by the 11% S figure)."
